# INTimeIntervalResolutionResult

**Class**

A resolution result for a time interval associated with an intent.

## Declaration

```swift
class INTimeIntervalResolutionResult
```

## Overview

An [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INTimeIntervalResolutionResult] object is what you return when resolving time interval related parameters of an intent object. Use the creation method that best reflects your ability to successfully resolve the parameter.

For additional resolution options, see [doc://com.apple.sirikit/documentation/Intents/INIntentResolutionResult].

## Creating a Resolution Result

- **success(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution involves the successful matching of the specified parameter.
- **confirmationRequired(with:)**: Creates an object whose resolution requires that the user must confirm the value before proceeding.

## Dates and Times

- **INDateComponentsRangeResolutionResult**: A resolution result for a range of dates in a parameter of an intent.
- **INDateComponentsResolutionResult**: A resolution result for the date information associated with an intent.

## Inherits From

- INIntentResolutionResult

- CVarArg
- CustomDebugStringConvertible
- CustomStringConvertible
- Equatable
- Hashable
- NSObjectProtocol
